    <Description>Per request from Thiep Nguyen, within this caldef updated the default value for the AHP_Horizon_Depth CAL from MPP_only to Navilink_only.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>4</Version>
    <Date>2016-06-14</Date>
    <Description>MY19 Updates by Andreas Klein: Add the following new calibrations: AHP_Content_MinMPPLength (Initial release of this calibration: This calibration was previously defined as an integer type calibration (CalID: _JuxRIL5BEeO1CZP5M-nrYg), and is being replaced in this release by the inital release of the AHP_Content_MinMPPLength defined now as an ENUM calibration (CalID: _HGgMwDISEeaowIzu94EMuA)), AHP_Content_MinSubPathLength (Initial release of this calibration: This calibration was previously defined as an integer type calibration (CalID: _OsvnAL5BEeO1CZP5M-nrYg), and is being replaced in this release by the inital release of the AHP_Content_MinSubPathLength defined now as an ENUM calibration (CalID: _RPVMADIUEeaowIzu94EMuA)), AHP_Enable_Extra_Segment_Message, AHP_Enable_System_Specific_Message, AHP_Enable_Checksum_Message, AHP_MPP_Learning_Mode_Enabled, AHP_Content_MaxNoStubs, AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP1_Curvature ( Initial release of this calibration: This calibration was previously defined as an integer type calibration (CalID: _yGLt4L5OEeO1CZP5M-nrYg), and is being replaced by the initial release of the AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP1_Curvature defined now as an ENUM calibration (CalID: _v4v-kDLTEeaZVPjYxm4yTA)), AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP21_ReservedSystem, AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP22_ReservedSystem, AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP23_ReservedSystem, AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP24_ReservedSystem, AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP25_ReservedSystem, AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP26_ReservedSystem, AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP27_ReservedSystem, AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP28_ReservedSystem, AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP29_ReservedSystem, AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP30_ReservedSystem, AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP31_ReservedSystem, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP8_TrafficSigns (Initial release of this calibration. This calibration was previously defined as an Integer type calibration (CalID: _iq_fMb_jEeO1CZP5M-nrYg), and is being replaced by the initial release of the AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP8_TrafficSigns defined now as an ENUM calibration (CalID: _mvZHQDIsEeaowIzu94EMuA)), AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP22_ReservedSystem, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP23_ReservedSystem, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP24_ReservedSystem, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP25_ReservedSystem, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP26_ReservedSystem, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP27_ReservedSystem, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP28_ReservedSystem, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP30_ReservedSystem, and AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP31_ReservedSystem. Deleted the following calibrations: AHP_Content_MinMPPLength (CalID:_JuxRIL5BEeO1CZP5M-nrYg), AHP_Content_MinSubPathLength (CalID: _OsvnAL5BEeO1CZP5M-nrYg), AHP_Content_MaxNoStubs (CalID: _VEr60cRzEeO68uG6rmzOVg), AHP_MaxNoPaths (CalID: _kBOsQMRrEeOT-aS2E2f1iQ), AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP1_CurvatureActive (CalID: _yGLt4L5OEeO1CZP5M-nrYg), and AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP8_TrafficSigns (CalID: _iq_fMb_jEeO1CZP5M-nrYg). Also, made the following updates to existing calibrations: For the ADASIS_SUPPORT calibration made the following updated the default value. For the TX_Multiplexed_Minimum_Update_Time calibration made the following changed the units to milliseconds. For TX_Multiplexed_Periodic_Rate calibration updated the Units to milliseconds and updated the default value. For TX_Debug_Delay_Initial_Transmission calibration the calibration name updated from Calibration name updated from TX_Debug_Delay_InitialTransmission to TX_Debug_Delay_Initial_Transmission, and updated the units to milliseconds. For the AHP_Tx_Meta_Message_Update_Interval calibration updated the calibration name from AHP_Tx_MetaMessageUpdateInterval to AHP_Tx_Meta_Message_Update_Interval, and the updated the  units, maximum value, minimum, and default values for this calibration. For the AHP_Tx_Position_Message_Update_Interval calibration updated the calibration name from AHP_Tx_PositionMessageUpdateInterval to AHP_Tx_Position_Message_Update_Interval, and the units, minimum, maximum, and default values for this calibration. For the AHP_Rx_Retransmission_Request and AHP_Debug_Enable_Visualization calibrations updated the calibration names. For the AHP_SecondHorizonOffsetResolution and AHP_TrailingHorizonLength calibrations updated the units, maximum, minimum, default, and resolution values. For the AHP_Content_MaxNoSegments calibration updated the calibration description, minimum, maximum, and default values. For the AHP_Horizon_Depth calibration updated the default value. For the AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP2_RouteNumber calibration updated the calibration name from AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP2_RouteNumberActive to AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP2_RouteNumber and updated the minimum and maximum values for this calibration. For the AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP3_SlopeStep calibration updated the calibration name from AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP3_SlopeStepActive to AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP3_SlopeStep and updated minimum and maximum values For the AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP4_SlopeLinear calibration updated the minimum and maximum values and calibration description. For the AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP5_RoadAccessability  and AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP6_RoadCondition calibrations updated the minimum and maximum values and calibration description. For AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP7_VariableSpeedSignPositions calibration name change from AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP7_VariableSpeedSigns to AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP7_VariableSpeedSignPositions and minimum and maximum values changed. For the AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP8_HeadingChange calibration updated the calibration description and minimum and maximum values. </Description>
    <Author>Andreas Klein</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>4</Version>
    <Date>2016-06-14</Date>
    <Description>MY19 Updates by Andreas Klein (continued): For the following calibrations the calibration name, calibration description, and minimum and maximum values were updated for the following calibrations: AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP16_TrafficLightPositionAndLaneValidity, AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP17_MajorOverheadRoadSigns, AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP18_StopLinesYieldLines, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP1_SPLongitude, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP2_SPLatitude, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP3_SPAltitude, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP4_CPLongitude, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP5_CPLatitude,  AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP6_CPAltitude, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP7_LinkIdentifier, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP9_TruckSpeedLimits, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP17_RoadSigns, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP18_LateralDistanceCurvatureToRoadCenter, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP19_AbsoluteLongitudePosition, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP20_AbsoluteLatitudePosition, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP1_SPLongitude, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP2_SPLatitude, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP3_SPAltitude, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP4_CPLongitude, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP5_CPLatitude, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP6_CPAltitude, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP7_LinkIdentifier, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP9_TruckSpeedLimits, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP17_RoadSigns, and AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP18_LateralDistanceCurvatureToRoadCenter, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP19_AbsoluteLongitudePosition, and AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP20_AbsoluteLatitudePosition. For the following calibrations updated the calibration description, minimum and maximum values: AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP10_ExtendedLane, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP16_LaneWidth, and AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP21_Timestamp. For the AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP19_ReservedSystem calibration updated the calibration name from AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP19_MajorOverheadSign to AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP19_ReservedSystem. For the the AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP20_ResrevedSytem changed the calibration name from AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP20_StopYieldLines to AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP20_ReservedSystem. For the AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP29_ReservedSystem calibration updated the calibration name from AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP22_RoadHeadingHD to AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP29_ReservedSystem.</Description>
    <Author>Andreas Klein</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>5</Version>
    <Date>2016-08-19</Date>
    <Description>Within this ADASIS.caldef file made the following updates: 1.) Update made to the ADASIS_SUPPORT enumeration values, 2.) Added new NAVILINK_ENABLED calibration, 3.) Deleted the AHP Horizon Depth calibration previously defined in this caldef file since it was confirmed this additional calibration separate from the ADASIS_SUPPORT calibration is not needed, 4.) Updated the units to meters, minimum, maximum, and resolution values for the AHP_TrailingHorizonLength calibration to correspond to the values shown in the GIS-628 specification for this calibration, 5.) Deleted the AHP_Content_MinSubPathLength calibration with CalID: _RPVMADIUEeaowIzu94EmuA that was initially incorrectly defined as an EnumFloatMap, and created a new calibration also called AHP_Content_MinSubPathLength with CalID: _001GwGYHEea-68x0t4hw1g to redefine this calibration as an Integer type calibration corresponding to how it is defined in the GIS-628 specification, 6.) Deleted the AHP_Content_MinMPPLength calibration with CalID: _HGgMwDISEeaowIzu94EmuA that was initially incorrectly defined as an EnumFloatMap, and created a new calibration also called AHP_Content_MinMPPLength with calibration with CalID: _SqI_EGYHEea-68x0t4hw1g to redefine this calibration as an Integer type calibration corresponding to how it is defined in the GIS-628 specification, 7.) Deleted the AHP_Content_MaxNoStubs calibration with CalID: _IHGtIDIdEeaowIzu94EmuA that was initially incorrectly defined as an EnumFloatMap, and created a new calibration also called AHP_Content_MaxNoStubs with CalID: _u_rtwGYGEea-68x0t4hw1g to redefine this calibration as an Integer type calibration corresponding to how it is defined in the GIS-628 specification , 8.) Deleted the AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP1_Curvature calibration with CalID: _v4v-kDLTEeaZVPjYxm4yTA that was initially incorrectly defined as an EnumFloatMap, and created a new calibration also called AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP1_Curvature with CalID: _J00swGYeEea-68x0t4hw1g to redefine this calibration as an Integer type calibration corresponding to how it is defined in the GIS-628 specification, 9.) Deleted the AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP8_TrafficSigns calibration with CalID: _mvZHQDIsEeaowIzu94EMuA that was initially incorrectly defined as an EnumFloatMap, and created a new calibration also called AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP8_TrafficSigns with CalID: _zWCYEGYIEea-68x0t4hw1g to redefine this calibration as an Integer type calibration corresponding to how it is defined in the GIS-628 specification, 10.) Updated the units to meters, minimum and resolution values for the AHP_SecondHorizonOffsetResolution calibration to correspond to the values shown in the GIS-628 specification for this calibration, 11.) Updated the calibration Usage type field for all of the ADASIS calibrations defined in the previous revision ADASIS.caldef file that had a Usage type of just High to show all of these calibrations as being needed for both Mid and High, 12.) Also updated the units shown for the Tx_Max_Offset_Range calibration,  from none to meters to reflect the correct intended representation of units for this calibration, and 13.) Also updated the units shown for the TX_Debug_Delay_Initial_Transmission calibration  from none to  milliseconds to reflect the correct intended representation of units for this calibration.</Description>
    <Author>Andreas Klein</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>6</Version>
    <Date>2017-06-02</Date>
    <Description>Added two boolean type calibration parameters (AHP_Tx_Enforced_Message_Priorities and AHP_Tx_Explicit_STUB_Removal_Messages), updated usage field for all calibrations within ADASIS.caldef file to support new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in CalDef tool, corrected Min/Max value for the following 34 calibrations: AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP10_Reserved, AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP11_Reserved, AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP12_Reserved, AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP13_Reserved, AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP14_Reserved, AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP15_Reserved, AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP19_Reserved, AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP20_Reserved, AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP21_Reserved, AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP22_Reserved, AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP23_Reserved, AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP24_Reserved, AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP25_Reserved, AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP26_Reserved, AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP27_Reserved, AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP28_Reserved, AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP29_Reserved, AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP30_Reserved, AHP_Content_MaxNo_SP31_Reserved, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP11_Reserved, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP12_Reserved, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP13_Reserved, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP14_Reserved, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP15_Reserved, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP21_Timestamp, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP23_ReservedSystem, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP24_ReservedSystem, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP25_ReservedSystem, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP26_ReservedSystem, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP27_ReservedSystem, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP28_ReservedSystem, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP29_ReservedSystem, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP30_ReservedSystem, AHP_Content_MaxNo_LP31_ReservedSystem within this caldef file to match with what was reflected in the released version of GIS-628 the suppliers currently have.</Description>
    <Author>Andreas Andrae</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>7</Version>
    <Date>27MAR2019</Date>
    <Description>Added 'ENTRY_VCU' and 'VCU' tags for initial creation of VCS compatible CalDefDatabase for version GIS-646 V6.0.0 release.</Description>
    <Author>Scott Rush</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefinition Description="Enables/Disables NAVILINK (independent of ADASIS_SUPPORT selection)." Name="NAVILINK_ENABLED" References="GIS-628 Appendix B" Usage="MID,HIGH,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,VCU">
    <CalID>_Yr4q4Ez0Eea8foBPr9M3iw</CalID>
    <Type>Boolean</Type>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>1</Version>
      <Date>2016-08-19</Date>
      <Description>Initial release of the NAVILINK_ENABLED calibration.</Description>
      <Author>Andreas Klein</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>2</Version>
      <Date>2017-06-02</Date>
      <Description>Updated default calibration value to TRUE. Updated usage field to support new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in CalDef tool.</Description>
      <Author>Andreas Andrae</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <Boolean>
      <Value>true</Value>
    </Boolean>
  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="see GDMPRS-923, main switch between ADASIS variants" Name="ADASIS_SUPPORT" References="GIS-628 Appendix B" Usage="MID,HIGH,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,VCU">
    <CalID>_yo_jQE1AEeO3UM5MzM17kw</CalID>
    <Type>Enumeration</Type>
    <Version>5</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>3</Version>
      <Date>2016-06-14</Date>
      <Description>Updated default value to MY19 default setting for Lean ADASIS is: MPP_WITH_STUBS </Description>
      <Author>Andreas Klein, GIS-628</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>4</Version>
      <Date>2016-08-19</Date>
      <Description>Updated the ADASIS_SUPPORT enumeration values and updated the usage type from High to Mid and High.</Description>
      <Author>Andreas Klein</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>5</Version>
      <Date>2017-06-02</Date>
      <Description>Updated usage field to support new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in CalDef tool.</Description>
      <Author>Andreas Andrae</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <Enumeration>
      <EnumID>_ypAKUE1AEeO3UM5MzM17kw</EnumID>
      <Value>2</Value>
    </Enumeration>
  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="3.4.3 Path Length Limits. The ADASIS concept uses different range values to define the length of the ADAS horizon. " Name="Tx_Max_Offset_Range" References="GIS-628 Appendix B" Usage="MID,HIGH,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,VCU">
    <CalID>_yrNw001AEeO3UM5MzM17kw</CalID>
    <Type>Integer</Type>
    <Version>3</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>1</Version>
      <Date>26AUG2013</Date>
      <Description>Initial import on from GIS-344 derived CSV file.  Original CALDS block=hmi_nav_sys_caln</Description>
      <Author>GIS-344 GIS-343</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>2</Version>
      <Date>2016-08-19</Date>
      <Description>Update the usage type from High to Mid and High, and update the units defined for this calibration to be meters instead of none.</Description>
      <Author>Andreas Klein</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>3</Version>
      <Date>2017-06-02</Date>
      <Description>Updated usage field to support new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in CalDef tool.</Description>
      <Author>Andreas Andrae</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <Integer>
      <Value>3000</Value>
      <MinValue>0</MinValue>
      <MaxValue>8190</MaxValue>
      <Units>m</Units>
      <Resolution>1.0</Resolution>
    </Integer>
  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="Minimal update interval to send any data on the horizon, shall be filled with retransmission, if no new data is available (see 7.3.4, GDMPRS-802)" Name="TX_Multiplexed_Minimum_Update_Time" References="GIS-628 Appendix B" Usage="MID,HIGH,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,VCU">
